{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JmV8MsKRTKoFcfx4oPhvsX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01M2MSs1siYH5myM8rgHiPLy","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Study DIAMOND codebase architecture","subagent_type":"Explore","prompt":"Very thoroughly explore the DIAMOND codebase at /root/research/diamond/ to understand its world model architecture. I need to understand:\n\n1. **World model class** — the part that takes (observation_history, action) → next_observation. What is the backbone? U-Net? DiT? Transformer?\n2. **Diffusion process** — noise schedule, denoising steps, loss function (continuous diffusion specifics)\n3. **Action conditioning** — how actions are conditioned (embedded and added? cross-attention? AdaLN?)\n4. **Data pipeline** — how Atari frames are preprocessed, stored, loaded (frame size, color space, normalization)\n5. **Training loop** — batch size, learning rate, number of steps for convergence, optimizer\n6. **Evaluation metrics** — PSNR, SSIM, LPIPS, FVD, or game-specific metrics\n\nLook at the README, config files, model definitions, training scripts, and data loading code. Report all findings with specific file paths and line numbers."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":331,"cache_read_input_tokens":24120,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":331},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6eb3f8f9-70a7-4c62-8ed1-8dd1b9e7b463","uuid":"976041b9-3a3e-43a7-99e1-7cfedd10a67d"}
