{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JdxWGX5JdWy8LY86pSFa6m","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Diffusion for World Modeling: Visual Details Matter in Atari (NeurIPS 2024 Spotlight)\n2\t\n3\t[**TL;DR**] 💎 DIAMOND (DIffusion As a Model Of eNvironment Dreams) is a reinforcement learning agent trained entirely in a diffusion world model.\n4\t\n5\t🌍 [Project Page](https://diamond-wm.github.io) • 🤓 [Paper](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2405.12399) • 𝕏 [Atari thread](https://x.com/EloiAlonso1/status/1793916382779982120) • 𝕏 [CSGO thread](https://x.com/EloiAlonso1/status/1844803606064611771) • 💬 [Discord](https://discord.gg/74vha5RWPg)\n6\t\n7\t<div align='center'>\n8\t  RL agent playing in autoregressive imagination of Atari world models\n9\t  <br>\n10\t  <img alt=\"DIAMOND agent in WM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eb6b72eb-73df-4178-8a3d-cdad80ff9152\">\n11\t\n12\t</div>\n13\t\n14\t<div align='center'>\n15\t  Human player in CSGO world model (full quality video <a href=\"https://diamond-wm.github.io/static/videos/grid.mp4\">here</a>)\n16\t  <br>\n17\t  <img alt=\"DIAMOND agent in WM\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/dcbdd523-ca22-46a9-bb7d-bcc52080fe00\">\n18\t</div>\n19\t\n20\tQuick install to try our [pretrained world models](#try) using [miniconda](https://docs.anaconda.com/free/miniconda/miniconda-install/):\n21\t\n22\t>```bash\n23\t>git clone https://github.com/eloialonso/diamond.git\n24\t>cd diamond\n25\t>conda create -n diamond python=3.10\n26\t>conda activate diamond\n27\t>pip install -r requirements.txt\n28\t>```\n29\t\n30\tFor Atari (world model + RL agent)\n31\t\n32\t>```bash\n33\t>python src/play.py --pretrained\n34\t>```\n35\t\n36\tFor CSGO (world model only)\n37\t\n38\t>```bash\n39\t>git checkout csgo\n40\t>python src/play.py\n41\t>```\n42\t\n43\tAnd press `m` to take control (the policy is playing by default)!\n44\t\n45\t**Warning**: Atari ROMs will be downloaded with the dependencies, which means that you acknowledge that you have the license to use them.\n46\t\n47\t## CSGO\n48\t\n49\t\n50\t**Edit**: Check out the [csgo branch](https://github.com/eloialonso/diamond/tree/csgo) to try our DIAMOND's world model trained on *Counter-Strike: Global Offensive*!\n51\t\n52\t```bash\n53\tgit checkout csgo\n54\tpython src/play.py\n55\t```\n56\t> Note on Apple Silicon you must enable CPU fallback for MPS backend with\n57\t> PYTORCH_ENABLE_MPS_FALLBACK=1 python src/play.py\n58\t\n59\t\n60\t<a name=\"quick_links\"></a>\n61\t## Quick Links\n62\t\n63\t- [Try our playable diffusion world models](#try)\n64\t- [Launch a training run](#launch)\n65\t- [Configuration](#configuration)\n66\t- [Visualization](#visualization)\n67\t  - [Play mode (default)](#play_mode)\n68\t  - [Dataset mode (add `-d`)](#dataset_mode)\n69\t  - [Other options, common to play/dataset modes](#other_options)\n70\t- [Run folder structure](#structure)\n71\t- [Results](#results)\n72\t- [Citation](#citation)\n73\t- [Credits](#credits)\n74\t\n75\t<a name=\"try\"></a>\n76\t## [⬆️](#quick_links) Try our playable diffusion world models\n77\t\n78\t```bash\n79\tpython src/play.py --pretrained\n80\t```\n81\t\n82\tThen select a game, and world model and policy pretrained on Atari 100k will be downloaded from our [repository on Hugging Face Hub 🤗](https://huggingface.co/eloialonso/diamond) and cached on your machine.\n83\t\n84\tSome things you might want to try:\n85\t- Press `m` to change the policy between the agent and human (the policy is playing by default).\n86\t- Press `↑/↓` to change the imagination horizon (default is 50 for playing).\n87\t\n88\tTo adjust the sampling parameters (number of denoising steps, stochasticity, order, etc) of the trained diffusion world model, for instance to trade off sampling speed and quality, edit the section `world_model_env.diffusion_sampler` in the file `config/trainer.yaml`.\n89\t\n90\tSee [Visualization](#visualization) for more details about the available commands and options.\n91\t\n92\t<a name=\"launch\"></a>\n93\t## [⬆️](#quick_links) Launch a training run\n94\t\n95\tTo train with the hyperparameters used in the paper on cuda:0, launch:\n96\t```bash\n97\tpython src/main.py env.train.id=BreakoutNoFrameskip-v4 common.devices=0\n98\t```\n99\t\n100\tThis creates a new folder for your run, located in `outputs/YYYY-MM-DD/hh-mm-ss/`.\n101\t\n102\tTo resume a run that crashed, navigate to the fun folder and launch:\n103\t\n104\t```bash\n105\t./scripts/resume.sh\n106\t```\n107\t\n108\t<a name=\"configuration\"></a>\n109\t## [⬆️](#quick_links) Configuration\n110\t\n111\tWe use [Hydra](https://github.com/facebookresearch/hydra) for configuration management.\n112\t\n113\tAll configuration files are located in the `config` folder:\n114\t\n115\t- `config/trainer.yaml`: main configuration file.\n116\t- `config/agent/default.yaml`: architecture hyperparameters.\n117\t- `config/env/atari.yaml`: environment hyperparameters.\n118\t\n119\tYou can turn on logging to [weights & biases](https://wandb.ai) in the `wandb` section of `config/trainer.yaml`.\n120\t\n121\tSet `training.model_free=true` in the file `config/trainer.yaml` to \"unplug\" the world model and perform standard model-free reinforcement learning.\n122\t\n123\t<a name=\"visualization\"></a>\n124\t## [⬆️](#quick_links) Visualization\n125\t\n126\t<a name=\"play_mode\"></a>\n127\t### [⬆️](#quick_links) Play mode (default)\n128\t\n129\tTo visualize your last checkpoint, launch **from the run folder**:\n130\t\n131\t```bash\n132\tpython src/play.py\n133\t```\n134\t\n135\tBy default, you visualize the policy playing in the world model. To play yourself, or switch to the real environment, use the controls described below.\n136\t\n137\t```txt\n138\tControls (play mode)\n139\t\n140\t(Game-specific commands will be printed on start up)\n141\t\n142\t⏎   : reset environment\n143\t\n144\tm   : switch controller (policy/human)\n145\t↑/↓ : imagination horizon (+1/-1)\n146\t←/→ : next environment [world model ←→ real env (test) ←→ real env (train)]\n147\t\n148\t.   : pause/unpause\n149\te   : step-by-step (when paused)\n150\t```\n151\t\n152\tAdd `-r` to toggle \"recording mode\" (works only in play mode). Every completed episode will be saved in `dataset/rec_<env_name>_<controller>`. For instance:\n153\t\n154\t- `dataset/rec_wm_π`: Policy playing in world model.\n155\t- `dataset/rec_wm_H`: Human playing in world model.\n156\t- `dataset/rec_test_H`: Human playing in test real environment.\n157\t\n158\tYou can then use the \"dataset mode\" described in the next section to replay the stored episodes.\n159\t\n160\t<a name=\"dataset_mode\"></a>\n161\t### [⬆️](#quick_links) Dataset mode (add `-d`)\n162\t\n163\t**In the run folder**, to visualize the datasets contained in the `dataset` subfolder, add `-d` to switch to \"dataset mode\":\n164\t\n165\t```bash\n166\tpython src/play.py -d\n167\t```\n168\t\n169\tYou can use the controls described below to navigate the datasets and episodes.\n170\t\n171\t```txt\n172\tControls (dataset mode)\n173\t\n174\tm   : next dataset (if multiple datasets, like recordings, etc)\n175\t↑/↓ : next/previous episode\n176\t←/→ : next/previous timestep in episodes\n177\tPgUp: +10 timesteps\n178\tPgDn: -10 timesteps\n179\t⏎   : back to first timestep\n180\t```\n181\t\n182\t<a name=\"other_options\"></a>\n183\t### [⬆️](#quick_links) Other options, common to play/dataset modes\n184\t\n185\t```txt\n186\t--fps FPS             Target frame rate (default 15).\n187\t--size SIZE           Window size (default 800).\n188\t--no-header           Remove header.\n189\t```\n190\t\n191\t<a name=\"structure\"></a>\n192\t## [⬆️](#quick_links) Run folder structure\n193\t\n194\tEach new run is located at `outputs/YYYY-MM-DD/hh-mm-ss/`. This folder is structured as follows:\n195\t\n196\t```txt\n197\toutputs/YYYY-MM-DD/hh-mm-ss/\n198\t│\n199\t└─── checkpoints\n200\t│   │   state.pt  # full training state\n201\t│   │\n202\t│   └─── agent_versions\n203\t│       │   ...\n204\t│       │   agent_epoch_00999.pt\n205\t│       │   agent_epoch_01000.pt  # agent weights only\n206\t│\n207\t└─── config\n208\t│   |   trainer.yaml\n209\t|\n210\t└─── dataset\n211\t│   │\n212\t│   └─── train\n213\t│   |   │   info.pt\n214\t│   |   │   ...\n215\t|   |\n216\t│   └─── test\n217\t│       │   info.pt\n218\t│       │   ...\n219\t│\n220\t└─── scripts\n221\t│   │   resume.sh\n222\t|   |   ...\n223\t|\n224\t└─── src\n225\t|   |   main.py\n226\t|   |   ...\n227\t|\n228\t└─── wandb\n229\t    |   ...\n230\t```\n231\t\n232\t<a name=\"results\"></a>\n233\t## [⬆️](#quick_links) Results\n234\t\n235\tThe file [results/data/DIAMOND.json](results/data/DIAMOND.json) contains the results for each game and seed used in the paper.\n236\t\n237\tThe DDPM code used for Section 5.1 of the paper can be found on the [ddpm](https://github.com/eloialonso/diamond/tree/ddpm) branch.\n238\t\n239\t<a name=\"citation\"></a>\n240\t## [⬆️](#quick-links) Citation\n241\t\n242\t```text\n243\t@inproceedings{alonso2024diffusionworldmodelingvisual,\n244\t      title={Diffusion for World Modeling: Visual Details Matter in Atari},\n245\t      author={Eloi Alonso and Adam Jelley and Vincent Micheli and Anssi Kanervisto and Amos Storkey and Tim Pearce and François Fleuret},\n246\t      booktitle={Thirty-eighth Conference on Neural Information Processing Systems}}\n247\t      year={2024},\n248\t      url={https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.12399},\n249\t}\n250\t```\n251\t\n252\t<a name=\"credits\"></a>\n253\t## [⬆️](#quick_links) Credits\n254\t\n255\t- [https://github.com/crowsonkb/k-diffusion/](https://github.com/crowsonkb/k-diffusion/)\n256\t- [https://github.com/huggingface/huggingface_hub](https://github.com/huggingface/huggingface_hub)\n257\t- [https://github.com/google-research/rliable](https://github.com/google-research/rliable)\n258\t- [https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch)\n259\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01M2MSs1siYH5myM8rgHiPLy","session_id":"6eb3f8f9-70a7-4c62-8ed1-8dd1b9e7b463","uuid":"27f3c679-dea4-48ba-9c45-966ecb169fb2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T08:29:16.913Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015qPEDSDF2U5n5eWYRegYRP","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tdefaults:\n2\t  - _self_\n3\t  - env: atari\n4\t  - agent: default\n5\t\n6\thydra:\n7\t  job:\n8\t    chdir: True\n9\t\n10\twandb:\n11\t  mode: disabled\n12\t  project: null\n13\t  entity: null\n14\t  name: null\n15\t  group: null\n16\t  tags: null\n17\t  notes: null\n18\t\n19\tinitialization:\n20\t  path_to_ckpt: null\n21\t  load_denoiser: True\n22\t  load_rew_end_model: True\n23\t  load_actor_critic: True\n24\t\n25\tcommon:\n26\t  devices: 0  # int, list of int, cpu, or all \n27\t  seed: null\n28\t  resume: False # do not modify, set by scripts/resume.sh only.\n29\t\n30\tcheckpointing:\n31\t  save_agent_every: 5\n32\t  num_to_keep: 11  # number of checkpoints to keep, use null to disable\n33\t\n34\tcollection:\n35\t  train:\n36\t    num_envs: 1\n37\t    epsilon: 0.01\n38\t    num_steps_total: 100000\n39\t    first_epoch:\n40\t      min: 5000\n41\t      max: 10000  # null: no maximum\n42\t      threshold_rew: 10\n43\t    steps_per_epoch: 100\n44\t  test:\n45\t    num_envs: 1\n46\t    num_episodes: 4\n47\t    epsilon: 0.0\n48\t    num_final_episodes: 100\n49\t\n50\tstatic_dataset:\n51\t  path: null  # if specified, will disable train/test data collection\n52\t  ignore_sample_weights: True\n53\t\n54\ttraining:\n55\t  should: True\n56\t  num_final_epochs: 50\n57\t  cache_in_ram: True\n58\t  num_workers_data_loaders: 0\n59\t  model_free: False # if True, turn off world_model training and RL in imagination\n60\t  compile_wm: True\n61\t\n62\tevaluation:\n63\t  should: True\n64\t  every: 10\n65\t\n66\tworld_model_env:\n67\t  _target_: envs.WorldModelEnvConfig\n68\t  horizon: 15\n69\t  num_batches_to_preload: 256\n70\t  diffusion_sampler:\n71\t    _target_: models.diffusion.DiffusionSamplerConfig\n72\t    num_steps_denoising: 3\n73\t    sigma_min: 2e-3\n74\t    sigma_max: 5.0\n75\t    rho: 7\n76\t    order: 1  # 1: Euler, 2: Heun\n77\t    s_churn: 0.0  # Amount of stochasticity\n78\t    s_tmin: 0.0\n79\t    s_tmax: ${eval:'float(\"inf\")'}\n80\t    s_noise: 1.0\n81\t\n82\tdenoiser:\n83\t  training:\n84\t    num_autoregressive_steps: 1\n85\t    start_after_epochs: 0\n86\t    steps_first_epoch: 10000\n87\t    steps_per_epoch: 400\n88\t    sample_weights: [0.1, 0.1, 0.1, 0.7]\n89\t    batch_size: 32\n90\t    grad_acc_steps: 1\n91\t    lr_warmup_steps: 100\n92\t    max_grad_norm: 1.0\n93\t\n94\t  optimizer:\n95\t    lr: 1e-4\n96\t    weight_decay: 1e-2\n97\t    eps: 1e-8\n98\t  \n99\t  sigma_distribution: # log normal distribution for sigma during training\n100\t    _target_: models.diffusion.SigmaDistributionConfig\n101\t    loc: -0.4\n102\t    scale: 1.2\n103\t    sigma_min: 2e-3\n104\t    sigma_max: 20\n105\t\n106\trew_end_model:\n107\t  training:\n108\t    seq_length: ${eval:'${world_model_env.horizon} + ${agent.denoiser.inner_model.num_steps_conditioning}'}\n109\t    start_after_epochs: 0\n110\t    steps_first_epoch: 10000\n111\t    steps_per_epoch: 400\n112\t    sample_weights: ${denoiser.training.sample_weights}\n113\t    batch_size: 32\n114\t    grad_acc_steps: 1\n115\t    lr_warmup_steps: 100\n116\t    max_grad_norm: 100.0\n117\t\n118\t  optimizer:\n119\t    lr: 1e-4\n120\t    weight_decay: 1e-2\n121\t    eps: 1e-8\n122\t\n123\tactor_critic:\n124\t  training:\n125\t    sample_weights: ${denoiser.training.sample_weights}\n126\t    batch_size: 32\n127\t    grad_acc_steps: 1\n128\t    start_after_epochs: 0\n129\t    steps_first_epoch: 5000\n130\t    steps_per_epoch: 400\n131\t    lr_warmup_steps: 100\n132\t    max_grad_norm: 100.0\n133\t\n134\t  actor_critic_loss:\n135\t    _target_: models.actor_critic.ActorCriticLossConfig\n136\t    backup_every: 15\n137\t    gamma: 0.985\n138\t    lambda_: 0.95\n139\t    weight_value_loss: 1.0\n140\t    weight_entropy_loss: 0.001\n141\t\n142\t  optimizer:\n143\t    lr: 1e-4\n144\t    weight_decay: 0\n145\t    eps: 1e-8\n146\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01M2MS