n depths: [0,0,0,0] (no self-attention in default config)\n  \n**Conditioning Mechanism:** **AdaLN (Adaptive Layer Normalization)**\n- Noise and action embeddings are concatenated and projected to produce condition vector\n- Condition is applied via AdaGroupNorm in ResBlocks (line 134-145 of blocks.py)\n- Formula: `x * (1 + scale) + shift` where scale and shift come from the condition embedding\n\n**Key Forward Path** (`inner_model.py` lines 44-49):\n```python\ncond = self.cond_proj(self.noise_emb(c_noise) + self.act_emb(act))\nx = self.conv_in(torch.cat((obs, noisy_next_obs), dim=1))\nx, _, _ = self.unet(x, cond)\nx = self.conv_out(F.silu(self.norm_out(x)))\nreturn x\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. DIFFUSION PROCESS\n\n**File:** `/root/research/diamond/src/models/diffusion/denoiser.py` and `/root/research/diamond/src/models/diffusion/diffusion_sampler.py`\n\n**Noise Schedule (Training):**\n- **Sigma Distribution:** Log-normal during training\n  - Location: -0.4\n  - Scale: 1.2\n  - Sigma min: 2e-3\n  - Sigma max: 20.0\n  - Computed via: `s = torch.randn(n) * 1.2 - 0.4; sigma = s.exp().clip(2e-3, 20)` (denoiser.py lines 52-59)\n\n**Sigma Schedule (Inference - Karras et al. schedule):**\n- Sigma min: 2e-3\n- Sigma max: 5.0\n- Rho: 7 (controls curvature of schedule)\n- Built via `build_sigmas()` (diffusion_sampler.py lines 61-66):\n  ```python\n  min_inv_rho = sigma_min ** (1 / rho)\n  max_inv_rho = sigma_max ** (1 / rho)\n  l = torch.linspace(0, 1, num_steps)\n  sigmas = (max_inv_rho + l * (min_inv_rho - max_inv_rho)) ** rho\n  ```\n\n**Denoising Steps (Default):**\n- Training: Variable sigma sampled from log-normal\n- Inference: 3 denoising steps (configurable via `num_steps_denoising`)\n\n**Loss Function: Continuous Diffusion (EDM - Elucidating Diffusion Models)**\n- **Noise Application** (denoiser.py lines 61-64):\n  - Offset noise: `offset = sigma_offset_noise * randn(b,c,1,1)` (sigma_offset_noise=0.3)\n  - Noisy observation: `x_noisy = x + offset + randn_like(x) * sigma`\n\n- **Conditioner Scaling** (denoiser.py lines 66-72):\n  - `sigma = sqrt(sigma² + sigma_offset_noise²)` (adjusted for offset noise)\n  - `c_in = 1 / sqrt(sigma² + sigma_data²)` where sigma_data=0.5\n  - `c_skip = sigma_data² / (sigma² + sigma_data²)` (skip connection scaling)\n  - `c_out = sigma * sqrt(c_skip)` (output scaling)\n  - `c_noise = log(sigma) / 4` (noise level embedding input)\n\n- **Loss Computation** (denoiser.py lines 114-116):\n  - Target: `target = (next_obs - c_skip * noisy_next_obs) / c_out`\n  - Model predicts denoising residual\n  - Loss: MSE between model output and target, masked by padding\n\n- **Denoise Function** (denoiser.py lines 87-91):\n  - Quantization to {0,...,255} then back to [-1,1]: `d = d.clamp(-1,1).add(1).div(2).mul(255).byte().div(255).mul(2).sub(1)`\n  - Ensures discrete 8-bit representation\n\n**Sampling Solver: Karras et al. 2-step method** (diffusion_sampler.py lines 30-58)\n- Supports Euler (order=1) or Heun (order=2) integration\n- Stochasticity control: `s_churn` parameter (default 0.0 for deterministic)\n- Time-conditioned noise injection: `s_tmin`, `s_tmax`, `s_noise`\n- Default config uses Euler method with no stochasticity\n\n---\n\n### 3. ACTION CONDITIONING\n\n**Location:** `/root/research/diamond/src/models/diffusion/inner_model.py` lines 27-30, 45\n\n**Method: Embedding + Linear Projection (combined with noise)**\n\n**Action Embedding:**\n```python\nself.act_emb = nn.Sequential(\n    nn.Embedding(cfg.num_actions, cfg.cond_channels // cfg.num_steps_conditioning),\n    nn.Flatten(),  # (b,t,e) -> (b, t*e)\n)\n```\n- Embedding dimension: `cond_channels // num_steps_conditioning = 256 // 4 = 64`\n- Flattened for temporal sequence: 4 timesteps → 256 dims\n\n**Conditioning Combination:**\n```python\ncond = self.cond_proj(self.noise_emb(c_noise) + self.act_emb(act))\n```\n- Noise embedding: Fourier Features (cond_channels=256 dims)\n- Action embedding: Flattened temporal embedding (256 dims)\n- Combined via addition, then projected through MLP:\n  ```python\n  nn.Sequential(\n      nn.Linear(256, 256),\n      nn.SiLU(),\n      nn.Linear(256, 256),\n  )\n  ```\n\n**Application: AdaLN in U-Net**\n- Condition applied to every ResBlock via `AdaGroupNorm` (blocks.py lines 34-45)\n- Produces scale and shift for group normalization\n\n---\n\n### 4. DATA PIPELINE\n\n**File:** `/root/research/diamond/src/envs/atari_preprocessing.py`\n\n**Frame Preprocessing:**\n- **Raw Atari Frame Size:** 210×160 RGB\n- **Resized to:** 64×64 RGB (configurable, default in config/env/atari.yaml line 4)\n- **Interpolation:** OpenCV INTER_AREA (cv2.resize)\n- **Max Pooling:** Over last 2 frames (pooling_buffer in preprocessing)\n\n**Color Space & Storage:**\n- **In-Memory:** uint8, range [0, 255]\n- **Normalized for Model:** float32, range [-1, 1]\n- **Normalization Formula** (episode.py lines 38-43):\n  - Load: `obs.div(255).mul(2).sub(1)` → `obs / 255 * 2 - 1`\n  - Save: `obs.add(1).div(2).mul(255).byte()` → reverse\n\n**Frame Skip & Life Loss:**\n- Frame skip: 4 (standard Atari)\n- Life loss handling: Can be toggled per environment (train: done_on_life_loss=True, test=False)\n\n**Batch Creation:**\n- Sequences are sampled from episodes with random offset\n- Segment length configured per model:\n  - Denoiser: `num_steps_conditioning + 1 + num_autoregressive_steps = 4 + 1 + 1 = 6` frames\n  - Reward/End: `horizon + num_steps_conditioning = 15 + 4 = 19` frames\n  - Actor-Critic: `num_steps_conditioning = 4` frames\n\n**Storage Format:**\n- Episodes saved as PyTorch dictionaries with hierarchical subfolder structure (dataset/train/0/0/0/0.pt, etc.)\n- Cached in RAM optionally for faster training\n\n---\n\n### 5. TRAINING LOOP\n\n**File:** `/root/research/diamond/src/trainer.py`\n\n**Batch Size & Learning Rates:**\n- **Denoiser:** batch_size=32, lr=1e-4, weight_decay=1e-2\n- **Reward/End Model:** batch_size=32, lr=1e-4, weight_decay=1e-2\n- **Actor-Critic:** batch_size=32, lr=1e-4, weight_decay=0\n\n**Optimizer:** AdamW with epsilon=1e-8\n\n**Training Schedule:**\n- **Denoiser steps per epoch:** 400 (after first epoch: 10000)\n- **Reward/End steps per epoch:** 400\n- **Actor-Critic steps per epoch:** 400\n- **LR warmup:** 100 steps for all components\n\n**Gradient Accumulation:** 1 (no accumulation)\n\n**Max Gradient Norm Clipping:**\n- Denoiser: 1.0\n- Reward/End Model: 100.0\n- Actor-Critic: 100.0\n\n**Collection & Training Loop** (trainer.py lines 209-263):\n1. Initial dataset collection with threshold (min reward diversity)\n2. Alternating collect & train phases over epochs:\n   - Collection: 100 steps per epoch\n   - Training: 400 denoiser + 400 rew_end + 400 actor_critic steps\n3. Evaluation every 10 epochs on test set\n4. Total training: ~50 final epochs after initial collection\n\n**Autoregressive Training:**\n- Denoiser uses 1-step autoregressive training (num_autoregressive_steps=1)\n- Model predicts next frame given previous frames and iteratively refines\n\n**Sample Weighting:**\n- Reward distribution balancing: [0.1, 0.1, 0.1, 0.7] (minority classes get lower weight)\n- Applied to batch sampling for diversity\n\n---\n\n### 6. EVALUATION METRICS\n\n**File:** `/root/research/diamond/src/trainer.py` lines 339-406, `/root/research/diamond/src/models/`\n\n**Denoiser (World Model) Evaluation:**\n- **MSE Loss:** Mean squared error between model prediction and target denoising residual\n- Logged as: `loss_denoising` (trainer.py, denoiser.py line 122)\n\n**Reward/End Model Evaluation:**\n- **Reward Loss:** Cross-entropy for reward classification (3 classes: -1, 0, 1)\n  - `loss_rew = F.cross_entropy(logits_rew, target_rew)` (rew_end_model.py line 77)\n- **End Loss:** Cross-entropy for episode termination (2 classes: 0, 1)\n  - `loss_end = F.cross_entropy(logits_end, target_end)` (rew_end_model.py line 78)\n- **Confusion Matrices:** Computed for classification accuracy breakdown (rew_end_model.py lines 85-87)\n  - Uses `torcheval.metrics.functional.multiclass_confusion_matrix`\n\n**Actor-Critic Evaluation:**\n- **Policy Entropy:** `entropy.detach() / log(2)` (normalized to bits, actor_critic.py line 91)\n- **Action Loss:** `-d.log_prob(act) * (lambda_returns - val).detach()` (policy gradient, line 84)\n- **Value Loss:** MSE between predicted and target returns (line 85)\n  - `weight_value_loss=1.0`\n- **Entropy Loss:** `-weight_entropy_loss * entropy` (line 86)\n  - `weight_entropy_loss=0.001`\n\n**Game Performance Metrics:**\n- **Episode Return:** Sum of clipped rewards (+1, 0, -1) per episode (episode.py line 34)\n- **Episode Length:** Timesteps until termination\n- **RL Agent Testing:**\n  - Tested in world model for 4 test episodes per evaluation\n  - Final test: 100 episodes for final return statistics\n  - Metrics: mean/std of returns (trainer.py lines 300-324)\n\n**Training Dynamics:**\n- Gradient norm before clipping: monitored per batch\n- Learning rate scheduling: LinearLR warmup then constant\n- Batch number tracking for per-batch metrics\n\n**No explicit PSNR/SSIM/LPIPS/FVD:**\n- DIAMOND focuses on reconstruction via MSE loss (not perceptual metrics)\n- Game-specific performance (return/episode length) is primary eval metric\n- Confusion matrices used for reward/end classification accuracy\n\n---\n\n## Key Files Summary\n\n| Component | File Path | Key Classes/Functions |\n|-----------|-----------|----------------------|\n| Inner Model (Backbone) | `/root/research/diamond/src/models/diffusion/inner_model.py` | `InnerModel`, `InnerModelConfig` |\n| Denoiser (Diffusion) | `/root/research/diamond/src/models/diffusion/denoiser.py` | `Denoiser`, `DenoiserConfig`, `Conditioners` |\n| Diffusion Sampler | `/root/research/diamond/src/models/diffusion/diffusion_sampler.py` | `DiffusionSampler`, `build_sigmas` |\n| U-Net Backbone | `/root/research/diamond/src/models/blocks.py` | `UNet`, `ResBlock`, `AdaGroupNorm`, `SelfAttention2d` |\n| Reward/End Model | `/root/research/diamond/src/models/rew_end_model.py` | `RewEndModel`, `RewEndEncoder` |\n| Actor-Critic | `/root/research/diamond/src/models/actor_critic.py` | `ActorCritic`, `compute_lambda_returns` |\n| Agent Wrapper | `/root/research/diamond/src/agent.py` | `Agent`, `AgentConfig` |\n| Trainer Loop | `/root/research/diamond/src/trainer.py` | `Trainer`, train/test methods |\n| Data Pipeline | `/root/research/diamond/src/data/dataset.py` | `Dataset`, `Episode`, `Segment` |\n| Batch Sampler | `/root/research/diamond/src/data/batch_sampler.py` | `BatchSampler` |\n| Atari Preprocessing | `/root/research/diamond/src/envs/atari_preprocessing.py` | `AtariPreprocessing` |\n| World Model Env | `/root/research/diamond/src/envs/world_model_env.py` | `WorldModelEnv`, `WorldModelEnvConfig` |\n| Config (Training) | `/root/research/diamond/config/trainer.yaml` | All hyperparameters |\n| Config (Agent) | `/root/research/diamond/config/agent/default.yaml` | Model architecture |\n| Config (Environment) | `/root/research/diamond/config/env/atari.yaml` | Frame size (64×64), env ID |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Diagram Summary\n\n```\nAtari Input (210×160×3)\n        ↓\n  AtariPreprocessing\n        ↓\n  Resize to 64×64, normalize to [-1,1]\n        ↓\n  Dataset → Episode Storage\n        ↓\n  BatchSampler (6-frame sequences)\n        ↓\n  Diffusion World Model:\n  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  │  InnerModel (U-Net)                     │\n  │  ├─ Input: [obs(t-3..t), noisy_next]    │\n  │  ├─ Noise Embedder: Fourier Features    │\n  │  ├─ Action Embedder: Embedding + MLP    │\n  │  ├─ Condition: AdaLN in ResBlocks       │\n  │  ├─ Core: U-Net [64,64,64,64] channels │\n  │  └─ Output: Denoising residual          │\n  │                                          │\n  │  Diffusion Sampler:                      │\n  │  ├─ 3 denoising steps (inference)       │\n  │  ├─ Sigma schedule (Karras, rho=7)      │\n  │  ├─ Euler integration                   │\n  │  └─ Quantization to [-1,1]              │\n  └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  